# Science Faculty Mentorship Program Knowledge Board

A digital online knowledge board system for the Science Faculty mentorship program to facilitate collaborative learning and engagement among mentor groups.

## Table of Contents

- [About](#about)
- [Features](#features)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
  - [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
  - [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)

## About

The Science Faculty is running a mentorship program where senior students mentor groups of first-year Science students during weekly mentoring sessions.
This digital knowledge board system aims to enhance these sessions by providing a digital platform for mentor groups to collaboratively document what 
they've learned on various topics, such as time management, study skills, and stress management.

## Features

- Create and manage knowledge boards for weekly mentoring sessions.
- Real-time collaboration with drawing, text, and file upload capabilities.
- User authentication for mentors and students.
- Analytics dashboard for program coordinators to track session engagement and participation.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following prerequisites installed:

- Node.js and npm
- MongoDB
- Your preferred web browser

### Installation

Follow these steps to install and run the project locally:

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
Github:
git clone https://github.com/LesleyShonz/MENTKNOW.git

GitLab:
https://gitlab.cs.uct.ac.za/shnles006/MENTKNOW.git

cd server
npm i
npm start

cd ..
npm i
npm start
```
